# Testing

## Process
- All non-trivial logic must have tests
- Write tests alongside implementation, not after
- Run tests before finalizing any module
- A task is only complete when tests pass

## Style
- Use Vitest with jsdom environment for DOM-related tests
- Prefer focused, fast unit tests
- Test behavior, not implementation details
- Use realistic inputs — not trivial "foo/bar" data
- Cover happy path and meaningful edge cases
- Avoid brittle tests that break on refactors
- Colocate test files next to the source they test

## What Must Be Tested
- DOM extraction
- Incident classification (all categories)
- Insight generation (summary, hypothesis, priority, useful frame)
- Sentry page detection
- Parsing helpers
